17/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Excavations will continue in Vlasic Mountain, where the remains of 52 people were exhumed by forensic experts last month, the local commission for missing persons announced on Sunday (August 16th).
More than 200 Muslims and Croats from the Bosnian city of Prijedor were allegedly taken to Koricanske Stijene on the mountain and killed by Bosnian Serb forces in 1992.
Their bodies were thrown down a deep ravine.
(Oslobodjenje, Onasa, Sarajevo-x.com - 16/08/09)
